      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARA'S PICKLE (1) had been going along well winning a Grade 6 three back then placing at this track before missing the frame latest when seventh (31.17) at this track. Better than latest and can atone here. APPEAL (5) is a handy dog who jumped from box 1 last time out and scored by 5.5 lengths at this track (29.79). Hard to fault her recent form and can win again. BONNIE IS BOUJEE (7) was drawn the middle but pinged the lids and led until the final stages, holding on for a place (30.13) at this track in a Grade 5 over 520m. Form is hard to fault from this box, with a win and six minor placings from seven starts. Can measure up. BURNT MARU (2) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
